cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with object part localization methods in computer vision, specifically in the areas of human pose estimation and face alignment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new measure called the "mirror error" and evaluates the performance of several state of the art algorithms, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the mirror error measure in guiding the selection of difficult samples and providing feedback in a popular Cascaded Pose Regression method for face alignment, indicating a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
